# Next.js 16 (App Router)

- **Server Components by default.** Add `'use client'` only when you need state, effects or
  browser APIs, and push it to the smallest leaf component.
- Fetch data in server components. Use `fetch` caching / `revalidate` (ISR) for external data
  (Sanity, TradeTracker) — pick a sensible revalidation window per source.
- Use the `Metadata` API for SEO (title/description/OG); no manual `<head>` tags.
- Use `next/font` (already wired: Fraunces + Inter as CSS variables) and `next/image` for
  media — never raw `<img>` for content images.
- App-specific UI composes shared components from `@odyssey/ui`; if a component is reusable
  across apps, add it to `@odyssey/ui` instead.
- Keep route handlers/server actions typed; never leak server-only secrets to client
  components (only `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` reaches the browser).
